data.title: Inside the Comms | Best of Stage 1
data.description: Put on a headset and join the teams on stage as we show the ups and downs of team communications throughout Stage 1 of the 2019 Overwatch League season.

data.title: Inside the Comms | Vancouver Titans
data.description: Whether talking about strategies, sweaty palms or spacing out, find out how the Vancouver Titans stay in sync during a match as we go Inside the Comms.

data.title: Bishop Leads Toronto
data.description: Coach Beom-joon “Bishop” Lee has had many ups and downs in the Overwatch League. From coaching the London Spitfire to stepping away from the game to comfort family, Bishop is ready for the next challenge with the Toronto Defiant.

data.title: Meta Report: Stage 1
data.description: Stage 1 of the 2019 Overwatch League was dominated by triple-tank, triple-support team comps. In this episode of the Intel Meta Report, learn the most important facts about the "3-3 meta" that you need to follow the action! It's all part of Insights: powered by Intel. Learn more at http://www.Intel.

data.title: Don’t Count Out the Outlaws
data.description: Can the Houston Outlaws make their way to the Stage 1 playoffs? The team that supports each other through thick and thin is ready to see what happens.

data.title: The Escape Room with the Guangzhou Charge
data.description: Representing 3 different countries and languages, the Guangzhou Charge have to build team synergy in-game AND overcome language barriers. Can Kyb, Onlywish, Chara and Shu communicate together well enough to find their way out of an escape room?

data.title: GOATS! GOATS! GOATS!
data.description: Whether you know it by “triple tank/triple support” or “3/3", there’s only way to pay tribute to the meta that’s defined Stage 1 of Overwatch League…with live GOATS!

data.title: Rookie Roundup with Kruise, Dogman, and Stratus
data.description: As new faces to the 2019 Overwatch League season, Paris Eternal’s Kruise, Atlanta Reign’s Dogman, and Washington Justice’s Stratus sit down to talk about finding roles within their teams, lessons learned from experienced Overwatch League players, and “trash talk” league-wide.
